MISCELLANEOUS DISMISSALS

2003-1164. In re Port.

This cause is pending before the court upon movant’s order to show cause why Lisa J. NAes should not be found in contempt for faAure to comply with subpoena duces tecum issued by the Board of Commissioners on Grievances and Discipline. Upon consideration of movant’s application for dismissal,

IT IS ORDERED by the court that the application for dismissal be, and it hereby is, granted.

ACCORDINGLY, IT IS FURTHER ORDERED by the court that this cause be, and it hereby is, dismissed.
